allowOverflow.description: Whether the panel should be strictly contained within the boundary when dragging

closeOnEscape.description: Whether the panel should close when the escape key is pressed

defaultOpen.description:
The initial open state of the panel when rendered.
Use when you don't need to control the open state of the panel.

defaultPosition.description:
The initial position of the panel when rendered.
Use when you don't need to control the position of the panel.

defaultSize.description: The default size of the panel

getAnchorPosition.description:
Function that returns the initial position of the panel when it is opened.
If provided, will be used instead of the default position.

getBoundaryEl.description:
The boundary of the panel. Useful for recalculating the boundary rect when
the it is resized.

gridSize.description: The snap grid for the panel

id.description: The unique identifier of the machine.

ids.type: Partial<{ trigger: string; positioner: string; content: string; title: string; header: string }>
ids.description: The ids of the elements in the floating panel. Useful for composition.

immediate.description: Whether to synchronize the present change immediately or defer it to the next frame

lockAspectRatio.description: Whether the panel is locked to its aspect ratio

maxSize.description: The maximum size of the panel

minSize.description: The minimum size of the panel

onExitComplete.description: Function called when the animation ends in the closed state

onOpenChange.description: Function called when the panel is opened or closed

onPositionChange.description: Function called when the position of the panel changes via dragging

onPositionChangeEnd.description: Function called when the position of the panel changes via dragging ends

onSizeChange.description: Function called when the size of the panel changes via resizing

onSizeChangeEnd.description: Function called when the size of the panel changes via resizing ends

onStageChange.description: Function called when the stage of the panel changes

open.description: The controlled open state of the panel

persistRect.description: Whether the panel size and position should be preserved when it is closed

position.description: The controlled position of the panel

present.description: Whether the node is present (controlled by the user)

skipAnimationOnMount.description: Whether to allow the initial presence animation.

strategy.description: The strategy to use for positioning

translations.description: The translations for the floating panel.
